Travel with Flair (TWF), a company in which former Miss SA and businesswoman Basetsana Kumalo is a minority shareholder, has been dragged into a legal tussle in the Polokwane High Court as unsuccessful local bidders challenge the awarding of a multimillion-rand tender. According to court papers seen by Sunday World, the applicants, who include 22 businesses under the Limpopo Travel Association Agencies (LTAA), applied for an interdict against Limpopo treasury department to restrain the department from implementing a tender awarded to TWF and Rakoma Travel. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD 